10/11/2002
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Bosnian Serb Interior Ministry announced Friday (8 November) that three senior officials have been arrested in connection with the illegal sale of aircraft spare parts to Iraq over the past four years. 
The suspects were identified as Milan Prica, the manager of the Orao aviation firm, assistant manager Teodosije Kecman and marketing manager Goran Santrac.
Also Friday, NATO announced that SFOR troops and local policemen raided three houses near the Serb town of Foca, and seized a significant amount of weapons and ammunition. 
(AP, AFP, NTV Hayat - 08/11/02)
